java.lang.Object
oogasalad.editor.controller.EditorObjectPlacementHandler
public class EditorObjectPlacementHandler extends Object

  • Method Details

    • placePrefab

      public UUID placePrefab(BlueprintData prefabData, double worldX, double worldY)
      Places a new object based on a prefab blueprint at the specified world coordinates. Creates the object, populates it, sets coordinates and name, and notifies listeners.
      Parameters:
      prefabData - The blueprint data for the prefab.
      worldX - The world x-coordinate for placement.
      worldY - The world y-coordinate for placement.
      Returns:
      The UUID of the newly placed object, or null if placement failed.

    • placeStandardObject

      public UUID placeStandardObject(String objectGroup, String objectNamePrefix, double worldX, double worldY, int cellSize)
      Places a new standard object with basic properties at the specified world coordinates. Creates the object, sets initial properties (name, group, position, size), and notifies listeners.
      Parameters:
      objectGroup - The group name for the new object.
      objectNamePrefix - The prefix for generating the object's name.
      worldX - The world x-coordinate for placement.
      worldY - The world y-coordinate for placement.
      cellSize - The default size (width/height) for the object's hitbox.
      Returns:
      The UUID of the newly placed object, or null if placement failed.
